Eight carts loaded with long-term food storage, kitchen utensils, clothes, blankets and other basic necessities 🌈 this is what the Bocconi community has donated to Pane Quotidiano Onlus, thanks to the "Christmas Charity Collection" initiative, set up by the associations @studentsforhumanity and @greenlight4business (with the support of @weexchangego ). The idea started off last year with two exchange students at Bocconi, Katya Berezovskaia and Julia Larkomaa, who started encouraging exchange students at Bocconi and off-site students to donate everything they couldn’t bring back with them, an idea which the associations are now using again for charity purposes. #Bocconi #charity #BocconiPeople #university #universitylife #studentlife #Milan

#LifeinDorms 🏠 What I miss most about life in residence halls is the possibility to 'go out and have fun with friends' in two minutes, simply by taking the elevator: when we were under stress for exams all we had to do was reach a common room to spend a few hours in company," says @francescasala____, who studies International Economics and Management. She used to share a room in the Bligny Residence with @alice.pomes, a third year student in Economia Aziendale e Management, now on an exchange in Madrid. "One of the most beautiful memories I have is her birthday party in the halls. We met in the shared kitchen with many other new students, coming from all over Italy: each of us cooked something different and we spent the evening sharing our ideas, expectations and fears. #Bocconi #residence #resicencelife #university #universitylife #studentlife #roomies #milan #BocconiBSc #BocconiMSc

Raise your hand if you like the new urban campus as much as we do 😍 The project includes a residence hosting 300 students, operational since the last academic year, the four buildings that make up the new headquarters of the SDA Bocconi School of Management and a multi-purpose sports center, functional starting in the next academic year. The latter has two swimming pools (one of which is Olympic-size 50m, the other 25m), a fitness area, a basketball/volleyball court and an indoor running track, with stands that can accommodate about a thousand people. Like the park, the sports center will also be open to everyone in the city. Check out our stories if you want to learn more. #Bocconi #weareopen #universirty #universitylife #studentlife #newcampus #campus #campuslife #architecture #archilovers #architecturephotography #building #city #milan #milanocity 📸: @paoton
